# Wallabag

# Alpine Linux


From the [installation requirements of
Wallabag](http://doc.wallabag.org/en/v2/user/installation.html#requirements),
the following PHP (\**sigh*\*) extensions are required (php >= 5.5 at time of
writing) :

>     php-session
>     php-ctype
>     php-dom
>     php-hash
>     php-simplexml
>     php-json
>     php-gd
>     php-mbstring
>     php-xml
>     php-tidy
>     php-iconv
>     php-curl
>     php-gettext
>     php-tokenizer
>
> wallabag uses PDO to connect to database, so you'll need one of:
>
>     php-pdo_mysql
>     php-pdo_sqlite
>     php-pdo_pgsql

The APKGBUILD used to build the php package on Alpine Linux is
[here](http://git.alpinelinux.org/cgit/aports/tree/main/php/APKBUILD)
